in this recipe, but feel free to use more or less based on your flavor preference.\u003c/p\u003e","equipment":["6\" small pot with lid","aluminum foil","baking sheet","potato masher (optional)"],"id":2035,"ingredients":["wild rice","sweet potato","ground turmeric","roasted salted almonds","lemon","red onion","baby arugula","unsalted butter","corn","dried cranberries","Champagne vinegar"],"ingredients_full":[{"name":"wild rice","quantity":"0.75","measurementUnit":"cup","displayOrder":1,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/498/medium_square_long-grain-wild1.jpg"},{"name":"sweet potato","quantity":"1.5","measurementUnit":"pound","displayOrder":2,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1272/medium_square_medium_square_sweet-potato-2.jpg"},{"name":"ground turmeric","quantity":"2.0","measurementUnit":"teaspoon","displayOrder":3,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/321/medium_square_tumeric-crop.jpg"},{"name":"roasted salted almonds","quantity":"2.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":4,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1342/medium_square_almonds_roasted_salted.jpg"},{"name":"lemon","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":5,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/16/medium_square_LEMON_SLICED_1_copy.jpg"},{"name":"red onion","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":6,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/90/medium_square_red-onion-cut-half.jpg"},{"name":"baby arugula","quantity":"3.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":7,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/239/medium_square_arugula-test.jpg"},{"name":"unsalted butter","quantity":"2.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":8,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/619/medium_square_dairy-butter-test.jpg"},{"name":"corn","quantity":"0.25","measurementUnit":"cup","displayOrder":9,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/487/medium_square_canned-corn-2.jpg"},{"name":"dried cranberries","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":10,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/104/medium_square_DRIED_CRANBERRIES_copy.jpg"},{"name":"Champagne vinegar","quantity":"0.5","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":11,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/252/medium_square_vinegar-champagne-2.jpg"}],"is_tastemaker":false,"upgradeable":false,"is_holiday_hack":false,"pantry_items":["olive oil","water","kosher salt","black pepper"],"pantry_items_full":[{"name":"olive oil","quantity":"3.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":3,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/267/medium_square_olive-oil-test.jpg"},{"name":"water","quantity":"1.5","measurementUnit":"cup","displayOrder":13,"imageUrl":"/assets/blank_profile-62376be1ebee267193d25c20f8cd8bc5a6c47743a4a323d32a54ecdf231b7b80.png"},{"name":"kosher salt","quantity":null,"measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":14,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/473/medium_square_kosher-salt.jpg"},{"name":"black pepper","quantity":null,"measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":15,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/493/medium_square_spice-black-pepper-test.jpg"}],"steps":[{"title":"Cook Wild Rice","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/16587/recipe_card_size_1._Cook_Rice.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003ePreheat oven to 450Â°F. In a small pot, combine \u003cstrong\u003erice\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e1.5 cups water\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat to medium low, cover, and simmer until water is evaporated and rice is tender, about 18 minutes. Remove pot from heat and set aside, still covered.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Roast Sweet Potatoes","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/16588/recipe_card_size_2._Roast_Potatoes_2X.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eWhile rice cooks, rinse \u003cstrong\u003esweet potatoes \u003c/strong\u003eand cut into .5-inch dice. On a foil-lined baking sheet, toss \u003cstrong\u003esweet potatoes\u003c/strong\u003e with \u003cstrong\u003eturmeric\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e1.5 tablespoons olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e,\u003cstrong\u003e .5 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003epepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired (see Recipe Tip). Arrange in a single layer and roast, tossing halfway through to prevent burning, until tender, 16-18 minutes total.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Prepare Ingredients","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/16589/recipe_card_size_3._Prepare_Ingredients.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eWhile sweet potatoes roast, roughly chop \u003cstrong\u003ealmonds\u003c/strong\u003e. Halve \u003cstrong\u003elemon\u003c/strong\u003e. Peel \u003cstrong\u003eonion\u003c/strong\u003e and cut half into small dice, saving remainder for another recipe (see Recipe Tip).\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Make Lemon Dressing","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/16590/recipe_card_size_4._Make_Dressing.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eRinse \u003cstrong\u003earugula\u003c/strong\u003e. In a medium bowl, whisk together \u003cstrong\u003e1 squeeze lemon juice \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003e.5 tablespoon olive oil \u003c/strong\u003eto fully combine. Season with\u003cstrong\u003e .125 teaspoon salt \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003epepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired. Add \u003cstrong\u003earugula\u003c/strong\u003e to bowl with dressing and toss to coat.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Mash Sweet Potatoes","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/16591/recipe_card_size_menu_small_5._Mash_Potatoes.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eWhen roasted, transfer \u003cstrong\u003esweet potatoes \u003c/strong\u003eto a separate medium bowl and add \u003cstrong\u003ebutter\u003c/strong\u003e. Using the back of a fork or a potato masher, mash until smooth. Season with \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003epepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired. Set aside.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Plate Wild Rice Bowls","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/16592/recipe_card_size_6._Plate_Grain_Bowl.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eAdd \u003cstrong\u003ecorn\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003ecranberries\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003eChampagne vinegar\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003ealmonds\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e1 squeeze lemon juice\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e2 tablespoons diced onion \u003c/strong\u003e(see Recipe Tip), \u003cstrong\u003e1 tablespoon olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e to pot with rice. Place over low heat and stir until corn is warmed through, about 2 minutes. Serve \u003cstrong\u003ewild rice\u003c/strong\u003e in bowls with \u003cstrong\u003eturmeric sweet potatoes \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003earugula\u003c/strong\u003e. Dig in!\u003c/p\u003e"}],"tags":{"all":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""},{"name":"No gluten ingredients*","slug":"no-gluten","hex_color":""}],"allergens":[{"name":"Milk","slug":"milk","hex_color":""},{"name":"Tree Nuts","slug":"tree nuts","hex_color":""}],"proteins":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""},{"name":"Loose Grain","slug":"loose-grain","hex_color":""}],"publicFacing":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""},{"name":"No gluten ingredients*","slug":"no-gluten","hex_color":""}],"feature":[]}}